race.comment: Winx's half-sister TIME OF MY LIFE (12) had a five-week freshen up before her last run, a comprehensive all-the-way win in a Class 1 over 1200m at this track. Drops 5kgs and with that run under the belt will again prove tough to catch. CARRAVILLA (3) opened this campaign with two wins then worked home well but found one better over 1400m at Eagle Farm last time out. The winner of two from two at Doomben. Has a wide alley to contend with but if things go right she can return to the winner's stall. NIGHTCAPPED (11) progressed in good style last start at the third run of the prep, easily accounting for a BM68 field over 1400m at the Sunshine Coast, albeit on a heavy track. Draws well and has nothing on her back so she should be in the finish again. SCUD (1) caught the eye over 1200m here recently when fresh from a six-week let-up. Fitter and will be hard to hold out over the extra 150m.
